-1 BLINK~

Blink is a mage-only spell that works like dodge or parry.  It kicks in 
automatically when you are in battle.  What happens is you learn how to 
shimmer out of existence, avoiding the blow from your attacker.  It also 
gives you a small bit of extra armor protection, from not quite being 
completely in reality.
~

-1 'DUAL WIELD' DUAL SECOND~

Syntax: second <weapon>

To hold a second weapon, you cannot be wearing a shield or holding an 
item in your other hand.  Also, since your offhand is weaker than your 
main hand, the weapon must be lighter.  Anyone can hold a second weapon, 
but only those skilled in dual wield can actually hit their target with 
it.  The higher it is, the more of a chance you have of hitting your 
target with the other weapon.
~ 

0 BUILDING CODING~

No, we don't need any more coders.  We can, of course, refer you to some 
other muds that do need them.

Yes, we can always use new areas, however, they have to pass a quality 
check, and no one can become a true Rivers of Blood builder (ie imm) 
without creating an area specifically for us that passes it.  If you want 
to create an area, great.  If it is reasonably decent and has a fantasy 
feel to it whose theme was approved, we'll put it in.  If you want any 
compensation for it, however, it has to pass the specs.

1) All rooms must have room descs that are at least 5 lines long.  Each 
room cannot have a desc just like another room in the area.  All exits 
must have exit descs.  Anything mentioned in the room desc must have an 
extra desc for it as well. 

2) All objects must have an extra desc for when you look at it.  Long 
desc doesn't count as this.

3) All mobiles must have look at descs of at least 5 lines.  There can 
only be one reset of each mobile.

4) Must have a reasonable number of rooms, to not skimp on distance (ie 
one room be a mountain, next be in the desert... should be some distance 
of rooms between the two.)

5) Theme must be approved beforehand.  If you fail to do this then you 
risk not having it approved.  Also, ask for some vnums or use QQ00, QQ01 
so find and replace can add the first 2 digits.

6) Area must be in Rom 2.3.  If not, it's up to you to convert it.

We don't give out any freebee imms.  You have to do this all beforehand 
before we give anything.  If you don't want to build up to these high 
quality standards, then we can always refer you to someone who is really 
desperate for builders.  We've learned in the past that people don't 
always do what they say they're going to do, so we want proof of hard 
work before we commit to anything.

Happy Building/Coding!
~


0 IMMQUEST~

Rules for Immortal Run Quests:

1) If it is not a quest for newbies and has a mobile involved DO NOT run 
it in any area not designed for it. I.e. Midgaard

2) No weapons as quest prizes.

3) No enchanting weapons higher than 10/10.

4) Equipment can be no higher than 30 levels above the winner's level.  
The eq level is the mobile it is found on, and not the level of the item 
itself.

5) No quests that discriminate against any one guild.

6) Quest prizes MUST be reasonable in total and not extravagant.

7) NO eq whatsoever is to be given out that comes from the automated
quests.
~

